        Using revolutionary technology, a fascinating documentary      
        explores the key political events and battles from WWII,       
        including Pearl Harbor, D-Day and Hiroshima.                   
                                                                       
        This two-hour H2 special uses an all-seeing CGI eye that       
        offers a satellite view of the conflict, allowing you to       
        experience it in a way that places key events and tipping      
        points in a global perspective.                                
                                                                       
        By re-creating groundbreaking moments that could never have    
        been captured on camera. By doing so it helps to illustrate    
        the importance of events happening in different places at the  
        same time and the hidden effects of crucial incidents.         
                                                                       
        WWII From Space presents the war's defining moments in a new   
        context and explains how a nation ranked 39th among the        
        world's military powers back in 1939,  emerged six years later 
        as the planet's only atomic superpower.
